## USER RESEARCH

**Top 5 Pain Points:**

1. **"Will short nails look too plain/basic for prom?"** — Core insecurity; readers fear they'll look underdressed compared to peers with long acrylic sets.
2. **"I can't grow my nails and I don't want fake extensions — what are my options?"** — Large segment who either can't wear acrylics (sport, work, health) or simply prefer natural length.
3. **"I don't know what shape to ask for when my nails are already short."** — Confusion about which shapes (square, oval, squoval) are available and flattering at natural length.
4. **"Will my nail polish chip halfway through prom night?"** — Durability anxiety about a full night of dancing, photos, and socialising.
5. **"My dress has a lot of detail — I don't know if I should keep nails simple or go bold."** — The dress-coordination problem is especially acute for short-nail wearers who feel they have less design flexibility.

**User Sentiment:** Aspirational but anxious — readers want validation that their natural length is beautiful, combined with concrete, specific design direction that removes the guesswork.

